\begin_layout Section
North Ameican Black and White Television (For Historical Purposes)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The picture is divided into 525 lines, which constitute a frame.Each frame
 is decomposed into two interlaced fields, each of which consits of 262.5
 lines.For convenience of presentation, we will we will refer to the two
 fields as I and II.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename Images/Engeneering/EE/Communication Engineering/ReducedSize/B&WRaster.jpg

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The time taken for each field to be scanned is 1/60 s .Correspondingly the
 time taken for a frame or a complete picture to be scanned is 1/30 s.
 With 525 lines in a frame , the line scanning frequency is 15.75 kHz.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thus , by flashing 30 stil pictures per second on the display tube of the
 TV receiver, the human eye perceives them to be moving pictures.
\end_layout

